description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit 1 part time administrator , working 22.5 hours to join the Adult Eating Disorder Service based at Jocelyn Solly House in Macclesfield. The days and hours of work have some flexibility and can be discussed further at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be highly organised and will need to provide an accurate and timely administrative service to the Eating Disorder Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The small team provides psychological and physical care to services users with moderate to severe eating disorders .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be required to demonstrate a high level of expertise in typing, keyboard and dictation skills which would include audio typing, together with knowledge and understanding of Microsoft packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will also need to be an effective communicator when dealing with service users, carers and health and social care professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits we encourage you to contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duncan Campbell-Team Manager or Dawn Mead-Team Secretary - Tel 01625 505620&lt;/p&gt;
